President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Dick Berner as the Director of the Office of Financial Research at the Department of the Treasury and Nancy J. Powell as the Ambassador to India at the Department of State. Berner currently works as Counselor in the Office of Research and Quantitative Studies at the Department of the Treasury and has held various positions in economics and finance. Powell, a career member of the Senior Foreign Service, currently serves as Director General of the Foreign Service and Director of Human Resources at the Department of State. She has also served as Ambassador to Nepal, Pakistan, Ghana, and Uganda, among other assignments.